review_blob: A nice IPA. Hoppy and bready, somewhat frutiy aroma, a dry finish and lasting aftertaste. Pours nicely with sark amber colour and a firm head. One of many top beers from S.Nevada.

First brew from this micro (actually a Swedish wine producer!). Unfortunately the high expectations, caused by the product deScription, falls flat to the ground. Its an unfiltered low carb brew, fresh and drinkable, albeit yeasty. But it lacks a lot of taste and aroma. Whats found is honey and hints of elder and black currant, but its hard to find. Colour is amber, hazy with a small head.

Bottle at Brewdock, Dublin. Amber colour, beige firm head. Very well balanced between caramel malt and citrus/flora hops, well marked bitterness, medium bodied and creamy, bitter long finish with great aroma that stays. On my top 5 of IPAs, very complex and enjoyable.

Bottle. Golden honey color, somewhat hazy (unfiltered?). Head is firm and tasty and really builds. Aroma of citrus and fruit, sweet malts. A crisp and lasting finish with aftertaste hoppy and herbal aftertaste. Has been one of my favourite pale ales fr fifteen years!

Bottle. Golden amber, off white, lasting head. Intense and rich floral hoppy aroma with hints of apricot, citrus and some pine. Pleasant, well marked bitterness. A very nice IPA, challenging the best from the USofA.

Labelled as Zatec Glutenfree. Golden with small, quickly disappearing head. Light aroma of bread, a bit watery and weak. Not the typical aroma and palate. One of the dullest czech beers I have sampled; is it the lacking gluten? Bit of a shame for the Saaz (Zatec) region.

Yet another "international lager" with absolutely no personality, or taste for that matgter. Watery, pale with diminishing head. The aroma there is contains hints of cardboard and...well overcooked veggies.

Mysteriously low RB rating... this is simply one of the best hoppy pilsners in the world! Dry and crisp, with a refreshing hoppiness and long aftertaste, fresh and clean with hints of mineral (due to the Friesland water used) and some grassiness. Attractive, firm white head. A perfect beer to just enjoy, slowly on its own, or with spicy food. A lot better on tap in Germany than from an exported bottle.

This is the classic schwarzbier stuff! Deep black to ruby red, a long lasting head. Really nice palate, nutty, roasted malts, hints of chocolate and a sweetness that is well balanced with the hops. A refreshing beer, though it looks "heavy", and one of my favourites. Furthermore; nice bottle design!
Certainly better than the Spendrups pale lager, but still nothin exceptional. It has a copper tone and more body, aroma and aftertaste is short.
Amber colour, nice appearance. One of the better 3,5 ABV beers on the Swedish market. A decent, albeit not thrilling, brew that works with food.
Well, it looks good but this so called red beer is a disappointment. Artificial flavour, short and metallic aftertaste. More body than other Harboe brews, but nothing to waste money on!
